                    <p class="mb-3">
                        VolunTrip started with a simple problem: volunteering abroad felt <strong>confusing</strong>.
                        Too many options, not enough clarity, and no easy way to know what’s legit.
                    </p>

                    <p class="mb-3">
                        In 2023, our founder <strong>Noam Levi</strong> (a backpacker with a laptop and a big spreadsheet)
                        tried to volunteer during a trip in Southeast Asia. After spending days comparing programs,
                        messaging organizations, and getting mixed answers, he realized: the missing piece wasn’t “more trips” —
                        it was <strong>better trust</strong> and a smoother process.
                    </p>

                    <p class="mb-0">
                        He built the first prototype from a hostel common room, tested it with friends, and kept improving it
                        until it became VolunTrip — a platform that helps people travel with purpose while staying safe,
                        organized, and supported.
